# Documentation with features

When you **add or change** anything user-facing or operator-facing in this repo, update documentation in the **same change** (do not wait for the user to ask).

## What to update

| Change type | Typical docs |
|-------------|----------------|
| New / renamed **env var** (`NEXT_PUBLIC_*`, service `.env`, systemd) | `README.md`, `docs/*.md`, relevant `services/*/README.md` |
| **API** routes, request/response shapes | Service README and/or `docs/` |
| **TTS / speech / rover** behavior | Repo root **`docs/tts.md`**, root **`README.md`** if quick-start env examples change |
| **Deploy** (ports, systemd, Docker, Jetson) | `docs/tts.md` or dedicated deploy doc, `deploy/` comments, root `README.md` troubleshooting |
| **Test UI** globals or HTML (`test_novabot.html`, `TTS.js`) | `docs/tts.md`, `services/llm-backend/README.md` |

Prefer **one source of detail** (usually `docs/`) and keep the root **README** to quick links, env one-liners, and troubleshooting tables.

## Tone

Short tables and examples; link to code paths. Avoid duplicating long prose in three places—link out instead.
